Arctic Monkeys postponed gig in Glasgow due to illness Alex Turners
The rock band Arctic Monkeys has postponed a concert in Glasgow, after their lead singer of inflammation of the larynx is ill.
The band from Sheffield should play in the water on Friday.
Due to the illness of the lead singer Alex Turner, the concert will now be moved, however.
The announcement of the band came after an earlier appearance in the LG Arena in Birmingham on Thursday had to move.
In a statement on their official website, the Arctic Monkeys: "After the decision, the show in the LG Arena in Birmingham to cancel tonight and on medical advice, the Arctic Monkeys, the show at the Hydro in Glasgow on Friday 1 November cancellations."
"Alex Turner was diagnosed with a throat infection, which is why he is unfortunately not occur."
The show in the LG Arena in Birmingham will now take place on 20 November, which was the Hydro in Glasgow on 21 November.
All tickets for those shows remain valid.
We apologize to all ticket holders for this inconvenience.
Please contact the sales department at the store where you bought your ticket, if you need further support.
